**Findings**
- `LOW` [behavioral-metrics design](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/docs/design/2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:452>): §12’s concrete built-in test list still stops at the original metric set. `commandValidationAcceptanceRate` and `executionFailureRate` are defined in §6.10/§6.11 and counted everywhere else as built-ins, but the test-target bullets never give them direct semantic cases; only the multiplexing bullet was updated to 11. §18’s generic “each built-in tested” clause keeps this below the reject bar, but the detailed test plan no longer fully round-trips the newest semantics fix.
- `LOW` [behavioral-metrics design](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/docs/design/2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:390>): the `SessionBundle` compatibility note still enumerates the pre-v3 field set as “all fields read by built-ins.” v4’s built-ins also rely on `commands[].result.accepted` and `executions[].executed` per [§6.10](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/docs/design/2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:241>) and [§6.11](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/docs/design/2026-04-27-behavioral-metrics-design.md:256>), and those fields are on the current bundle surface in [session-bundle.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/session-bundle.ts:46>) and [session-bundle.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/session-bundle.ts:118>).

`ACCEPT.` The iter-3 reject items are fixed: `null` replaces `NaN` in the test plan, the 11-built-in count is consistent in the touched sections, ADR 24’s field list is updated, the brace-expansion path is gone, the §8 volatile-metadata sentence no longer mispoints at §6.12, and the future async row now matches ADR 26. The engine-fact references behind the validator/execution split also still match current code in [world.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/world.ts:740>), [world.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/world.ts:1686>), [world.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/world.ts:1721>), [world.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/world.ts:1769>), and [session-recorder.ts](</C:/Users/38909/Documents/github/civ-engine/src/session-recorder.ts:163>).
